  "prompt": "What is an expression analogous to rest in peace in Hinduism?",
  "response": "In Hinduism, an expression analogous to \"rest in peace\" is \"Shanti\" or \"Om Shanti.\" This phrase is often used to wish peace upon the departed soul. \"Shanti\" means peace, and it is frequently invoked in prayers and rituals for the deceased, expressing a hope that their spirit finds tranquility in the afterlife. Additionally, the phrase \"Tathastu,\" meaning \"so be it,\" can also be used in a similar context to convey blessings for peace.",
